Name: The Griffonshire Sewers
Author: Crypticant
Description: Beneath the city of Griffonshire, this elaborate sewer system spans miles.

Rooms.Name: Outside a Massive Sewer
Rooms.Description: You see a large sewer pipe that is covered in grime and dirt. There is a strong smell of sewage and waste. You see rats scurrying around and hear the sound of dripping water. The ground is wet and slippery.

Rooms.Name: A Wide Sewer Tunnel
Rooms.Description: You see a wide sewer tunnel that is full of sewage. The tunnel is dark and smells bad. There are rats running around. The floor is slippery.

Rooms.Name: Higher Ground in the Sewer
Rooms.Description: You see a long, dark tunnel with a stream of sewage running through the middle. The walls are covered in slime and there are rats scurrying around. The air is thick and smells terrible. You hear the sound of dripping water and the occasional squeak of a rat.

Rooms.Name: Higher Ground in the Sewer
Rooms.Description: You see a long, dark tunnel. The walls are made of a strange, glowing metal. There is a faint light coming from ahead. You can hear the sound of water flowing somewhere.

Rooms.Name: A Rocky Cave Passageway
Rooms.Description: You see a rocky cave passageway that is dimly lit by a few small windows. The walls are made of rough, jagged stone and there are small puddles of water on the floor. The passageway is narrow and you have to be careful not to scrape your arms or legs on the sharp edges of the rock. As you walk, you can hear the sound of dripping water echoing off the walls.

Rooms.Name: A Dank Tunnel
Rooms.Description: You see a dank tunnel that is dark and musty. There is a faint light at the end of the tunnel, but you can't see what is causing it. There is a strange sound coming from the darkness, and you can't tell what it is.

Rooms.Name: A Very Wet Tunnel
Rooms.Description: You see a very wet tunnel that is full of water. The water is up to your knees and it is flowing very quickly. The tunnel is dark and you can barely see anything in front of me. You are holding onto a handrail to keep from slipping.

Rooms.Name: Beneath a Bathhouse
Rooms.Description: You see a large number of people walking above in the city. This drainage is for a large bathhouse in the center of the city. There are also many people in the city who are bathing in the baths.

Rooms.Name: The Sound of Dripping Water
Rooms.Description: You are near a small, secluded waterfall located beneath the sewer. The waterfall is surrounded by tall cliffs. The waterfall cascades down a series of rocks into a small pool below, where visitors can cool off on hot summer days.

Rooms.Name: Beneath the Latrines
Rooms.Description: You see a large open space with a few scattered trees and bushes. There is a path made of packed dirt that winds its way through the space. On either side of the path are latrines, each with a privacy screen around it. There are also a few small buildings that you assume are for storage or other purposes. The whole area has a feeling of being well-used but also well-cared for.

Rooms.Name: Beneath the Latrines
Rooms.Description: Above you see a busy city street with people walking and horses driving by. The street is lined with buildings on either side, and there is a large open sewer running down the middle of the street. The smell of the sewer is overpowering, and you can see rats running around in it. The sight and smell of the sewer is so disgusting that you can't help but hold your breath as you walk by.

Rooms.Name: A Rocky Cave Passageway
Rooms.Description: You see a dark and narrow cave passageway. The walls are rough and jagged. There is a small stream of water flowing through the middle of the passageway. You see some bats hanging from the ceiling. You also see some small creatures scurrying around in the shadows.

Rooms.Name: A Dank Tunnel
Rooms.Description: You see a dank, dark, and dirty tunnel that smells strongly of sewage. There is graffiti on the walls, and trash on the ground. The only light comes from the occasional street lamp, and it is very dim. You feel unsafe walking in this tunnel, and you hurry through it as quickly as possible.

Rooms.Name: A Very Wet Tunnel
Rooms.Description: You see a dark, wet tunnel with a small puddle of water in the center. The walls are covered in green slime and there is a faint smell of sewage. You hear the sound of dripping water and the occasional rat scurrying by.

Rooms.Name: A Narrow Cave Passage
Rooms.Description: You see a narrow cave passage that is carved into the side of a cliff. The passage is lit by torches that are placed along the walls. You think you can hear the sound of their footsteps echoing through the passage.

Rooms.Name: A Wide, Rocky Cave
Rooms.Description: You see a wide, rocky cave in the city. It is dark and there is a small stream of water running through it. There are some bats flying around and you can hear them squeaking. It smells damp and musty in here.

Rooms.Name: Amongst the Rubble
Rooms.Description: You see a tunnel that has been destroyed by something. The walls are in ruins, and the ground is filled with rubble. There are no people around, and the only sound is the sound of the wind.

Rooms.Name: A Dank Tunnel
Rooms.Description: You see a dank, dark tunnel that smells strongly of mold and mildew. There is a small puddle of water on the ground that looks stagnant. The walls are covered in grime and there is a general feeling of grime and dirtiness.

Rooms.Name: The Northern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: The northern sewer pipe is a dark and dreary place. The only light comes from the occasional street lamp or light from a nearby building. The pipe is wet and slimy, and the smell is incredibly foul. Despite all of this, there is a feeling of safety in the pipe, as if nothing can hurt you while you're inside.

Rooms.Name: A Very Wet Tunnel
Rooms.Description: You see a very wet tunnel that is full of water. The water is up to your ankles and it is flowing quickly. The tunnel is dark and you can barely see where you are going. You are holding on to the railings to keep from slipping.

Rooms.Name: A Sandhog Shelter
Rooms.Description: You see a sandhog shelter in the sewer. It is a small, dark, and cramped space. There are many sandhogs living in the shelter. They are all cramped together and it is very dirty.

Rooms.Name: Amongst Wastewater
Rooms.Description: You see a sewer that is full of waste and pollution. The air is thick with smog and the ground is covered in trash. The waterways are full of sewage and industrial waste.

Rooms.Name: A Columned Cave Entrance
Rooms.Description: You see a large, ancient cave entrance with many columns lining the front. The columns are carved with intricate designs and stand tall and proud. The cave entrance is dark and mysterious, inviting you to explore its depths.

Rooms.Name: A Westward Turn in the Sewer
Rooms.Description: You see a large, dark tunnel that seems to twist and turn. There is a faint light at the end of the tunnel, but it is hard to see. There are also some strange noises coming from the sewer.

Rooms.Name: A Cave-In
Rooms.Description: You see a cave-in the sewer. There is rubble everywhere and the pipe is blocked off. It's mostly quiet. You see a few rats that are either crushed or dying. It's a mess.

Rooms.Name: The Northern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large pipe that is full of sewage. The pipe is made of concrete and is approximately four feet in diameter. There is a small amount of water in the pipe, but it is mostly full of sewage. The pipe is dark and smells bad. There is a ladder leading up to a manhole cover.

Rooms.Name: A Narrow Sewer Passage
Rooms.Description: You see a narrow, dark, and wet sewer passage. There is a strong smell of sewage and you can see rats running around. The passage is slippery and there is a strong possibility of getting lost.

Rooms.Name: Murky Waters
Rooms.Description: You see a dark, murky body of water with debris and trash floating on the surface. The water is stagnant and smells bad. There are no fish or other aquatic life visible in the water. The banks of the waterway are overgrown with weeds and trash.

Rooms.Name: A Black Pool in the Sewer
Rooms.Description: You see a black pool of water in the sewer. The water is stagnant and smells bad. There is trash floating in the water. The sides of the pool are slimy and there are rats swimming in the water.

Rooms.Name: A North-South Drainage Pipe
Rooms.Description: You am walking in or along a north-south drainage pipe in the sewer. You see a pipe that is meant to drain water away from the city. It is made of concrete and is large enough for a person to walk through. There is a grate at the bottom of the pipe that allows water to drain out.

Rooms.Name: A Crumbling Tunnel
Rooms.Description: You see a crumbling tunnel that is in disrepair. The walls are cracked and the ceiling is caving in. There is trash and debris everywhere. The floor is uneven and there is water pooled in places. It is dark and dreary in here.

Rooms.Name: The Northern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large pipe that is full of sewage. The pipe is dark and smells bad. There is a small stream of water that flows through the pipe. You see rats and bugs crawling around in the pipe.

Rooms.Name: A Small Sewer Opening
Rooms.Description: You see a small sewer opening in the sewer. There is a faint smell of sewage, but it is not overpowering. You can see a few rats scurrying around, and there is a small puddle of water on the ground. The opening is small, and you have to stoop down to get through it.

Rooms.Name: Dark Waters
Rooms.Description: You see a narrow, dark river winding its way through a desolate landscape. The river is bordered by stone pipes, and there are no trees or other vegetation in sight. The only light comes from your torch.

Rooms.Name: A North-South Drainage Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a pipe that is meant to drain water. It is likely made of concrete or metal and is likely to be dirty and full of debris.

Rooms.Name: The Western Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large, dark pipe that is slightly wet. There is a small stream of water flowing through it. The pipe is made of concrete and is about four feet in diameter. There are no people or animals around.

Rooms.Name: The Western Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large pipe with a diameter of about eight feet. The pipe is made of concrete and is covered with a greenish-brown slime. There is a strong smell of sewage coming from the pipe. There are rats scurrying around in the pipe.

Rooms.Name: The Western Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large, concrete pipe that is meant to transport sewage away from homes and businesses. The pipe is dirty and there is a strong smell of sewage. There are rats and other vermin running around, and the pipe is dark and damp.

Rooms.Name: The Western Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large pipe that is discharging sewage into the ocean. There is a strong smell of sewage and there is a lot of trash and debris around the pipe.

Rooms.Name: The Western Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large pipe that is full of sewage and other waste. The pipe is dark and dreary, and it smells bad. There is a small stream of water flowing through the pipe, and you can see rats and other small animals scurrying around.

Rooms.Name: A Large Stone Drainage Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a concrete drainage ditch that is about four feet deep and ten feet wide. The ditch is lined with concrete and has a metal grate on the bottom. There is a pipe that goes from the grate to a storm sewer. There is a small amount of water in the ditch, and there is some debris on the bottom.

Rooms.Name: The Eastern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a dark, dank sewer pipe that smells of sewage and is full of garbage. You see rats scurrying around and occasionally see a homeless person sleeping in the pipe.

Rooms.Name: A Fountain Drainage
Rooms.Description: You see a concrete drainage ditch with a metal grate over the top. The water is flowing quickly through the ditch and there is debris caught in the grate.

Rooms.Name: The Eastern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a dark, dank sewer pipe that smells of sewage and is filled with trash. You see rats scurrying around, and you hear the sound of dripping water. The pipe is narrow and you have to watch your step to avoid tripping. The light from the manhole above is the only source of light, and it is dim.

Rooms.Name: The Eastern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: The eastern sewer pipe is a large pipe that runs through the city. It is dark and wet inside, and there is a strong smell of sewage. You can see rats running around, and there is trash and debris scattered everywhere. The pipe is large enough for you to stand up in, but you have to be careful not to slip and fall.

Rooms.Name: Dark Waters
Rooms.Description: You see a rushing river, flanked by rocks and trees. The river is dark and deep, and the water is cold and clear. The air is damp and cool, and the mist from the waterfall is refreshing. You hear the sound of the waterfall and the rush of the water, and you see the spray from the waterfall. The ground is slippery and wet, and you have to be careful not to slip.

Rooms.Name: A Narrow Gap in the Sewer
Rooms.Description: You see a narrow gap in the sewer. There is a small amount of water in the bottom of the sewer. You can see rats running around in the sewer. The smell of the sewer is very strong. You can hear the sound of rats running around in the sewer.

Rooms.Name: A Stone Basin
Rooms.Description: You see a stone basin that is surrounded by concrete pillars. The basin is filled with water and there are filthy ducks swimming in it. There is a path that goes around the basin.

Rooms.Name: The Entrance to the Sewers
Rooms.Description: You see a dark and dreary sewer system that is in desperate need of repair. The walls are caked with grime and the water is murky. There is a strong smell of sewage and garbage. You see rats scurrying around and occasional glimpses of human activity. The sewers are not a place for the faint of heart.

Rooms.Name: Dark Waters
Rooms.Description: You are walking along the water's edge on a small catwalk. The water is dark and murky and filled with trash. The smell of sewage fills your nose.

Rooms.Name: A Small Stream
Rooms.Description: You see a small stream of water trickling down through the rocks. The water is clear and cool, and the air is fresh and clean. You see trees and plants growing along the banks of the stream, and the sunlight shining through the leaves. You hear the sound of the water flowing and the birds singing in the trees. You feel the coolness of the water and the warmth of the sun on your skin.

Rooms.Name: A Drainage Sluice
Rooms.Description: You am walking in a drainage sluice in the sewer. You see concrete walls on either side of you, and a metal grate under your feet. Water is flowing through the sluice, and you can see trash and debris floating in it. The air smells damp and musty.

Rooms.Name: A Wide Sewage Drain Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a wide sewage drain pipe in the sewer. It is made of concrete and is about six feet in diameter. There is a small hole in the top of the pipe that leads down into the pipe. The pipe is filled with water and sewage. There is a strong smell of sewage coming from the pipe.

Rooms.Name: A Raft of Garbage
Rooms.Description: You see a large raft of garbage floating in the sewer. There is trash and debris everywhere. The water is dirty and there is a foul smell. You see rats and other vermin scurrying around. The raft is slowly moving and is a danger to navigation.

Rooms.Name: The Smell of Sewage
Rooms.Description: While walking in or along in the sewer, you see a lot of trash and filth. There is a strong smell of sewage and it is very unpleasant. You also see a lot of rats and cockroaches running around. Overall, it is a very dirty and unpleasant place.

Rooms.Name: A Small Stream
Rooms.Description: You see a small stream flowing down a waterfall valley. The stream is flanked by rocks and trees, and the sound of the water flowing is soothing. The air is fresh and clean, and the sun is shining down through the trees.

Rooms.Name: The Western Drainage Pipe
Rooms.Description: The western drainage pipe is a concrete channel that carries stormwater runoff from Griffonshire. The channel is lined with concrete and is approximately six feet wide and four feet deep. There is a concrete wall on one side of the channel and a chain-link fence on the other side. The channel is typically dry, but during heavy rains, water flows through the pipe and out to the ocean.

Rooms.Name: A Massive Drainage Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large, dark drainage pipe that appears to be made of concrete. There is a small stream of water flowing through it, and the pipe is surrounded by a concrete walkway. The pipe is large enough for a person to walk through, and there are metal handrails on either side.

Rooms.Name: Knee-Deep Water
Rooms.Description: You see water that is knee-deep, and it is murky. There is vegetation growing in the water, and you can see fish swimming around. Your torch light is reflected in the dark water.

Rooms.Name: An Abandoned Tenement
Rooms.Description: You see an old, abandoned tenement in the sewer. It is rundown and in disrepair. There are no people around, and the only sound is the wind blowing through the empty windows. The tenement is a sad and lonely place.

Rooms.Name: A Hidey Hole
Rooms.Description: You see a wide concrete sewer. Amid all the sewage and darkness, there is a small alleyway that looks like a hidden oasis. The alley is lined with trees and flowers, and there is a small fountain in the center. It looks like a peaceful place to take a break from the disgusting sewers.

Rooms.Name: A Westerly Drain Tunnel
Rooms.Description: You see a dark, wet, and narrow tunnel. The walls are made of concrete and there is a small stream of water flowing through the middle of the tunnel. The tunnel is dimly lit by a few overhead lights. There is a faint smell of sewage in the air.

Rooms.Name: A Crossroads in the Sewer
Rooms.Description: You see a large, open sewer with a deep trench running through the center. The trench is filled with waste and refuse, and the sides are lined with grates. There is a strong smell of sewage and rotting garbage. The ground is wet and slippery, and there are rats scurrying about.

Rooms.Name: An Easterly Drain Tunnel
Rooms.Description: You see a long, dark tunnel with a concrete floor and walls. There is a small stream of water running down the center of the tunnel. There are pipes and running along the walls. There are small puddles of water on the floor. There is a strong smell of sewage and mold.

Rooms.Name: A Crack in the Cave
Rooms.Description: You see a large crack in the cave wall with light shining through from the other side. There is a small pool of water at the bottom of the crack. You can hear the sound of water dripping from the other side.

Rooms.Name: A Drainage Sluice
Rooms.Description: You see a large metal grate in the ground with water rushing through it. The water is murky and there is debris floating in it. The grate is surrounded by concrete and there is a metal railing next to it.

Rooms.Name: A Narrow Stone Hallway
Rooms.Description: You see a long, thin hallway made of stone. It is narrow, and you can see footprints where there have been many people walking along it.

Rooms.Name: A Small Dirt Entrance
Rooms.Description: You see a small dirt entrance in the sewer. There is a concrete sidewalk leading up to it and a metal gate blocking the way. On the other side of the gate, you see a small dirt path leading into darkness. There seem to be trees and bushes around the perimeter of the path.

Rooms.Name: A Crumbling Sewer Passage
Rooms.Description: You see a dark and dank sewer passage that is slowly crumbling away. There is a faint light coming from somewhere up ahead, and you can hear the sound of running water. The air is thick with the smell of sewage and mold, and you can see rats scurrying around in the shadows.

Rooms.Name: A Freshly Patched Sewer Drain
Rooms.Description: You see a freshly patched sewer drain in the sewer. The patch is new and the surrounding area is clean. There is no debris or garbage around the drain. The patch is even and the edges are well defined. There is no water or sewage flowing from the drain.

Rooms.Name: A Small Stream
Rooms.Description: You see a small stream flowing through beneath the caverns. The stream is lined with rocks and moss, and there is a waterfall at the end. The caverns are dark and cool, and the stream is refreshing.

Rooms.Name: Within a Grand Cave
Rooms.Description: You see an expansive cave with numerous tunnels leading off in different directions. There are many bones and skeletons scattered about, as well as some ancient looking coffins. It is clear that this cave was once used as a burial ground for the city's dead.

Rooms.Name: A Dry Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a dry sewer pipe in the city. It is made of concrete and is about two feet in diameter. There is a small hole in the side of the pipe that goes into a manhole. The pipe is about four feet long and goes into a storm drain.

Rooms.Name: A Dry Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a dry sewer pipe in the city. It is made of concrete and is about four feet in diameter. There is a small hole in the side of the pipe, and a stream of water is flowing out of it. The water is clear and there are no fish or other creatures in it. The pipe is surrounded by a concrete wall.

Rooms.Name: A Dry Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a dry sewer pipe that is full of debris. There is a foul odor coming from the pipe. You see rats running around in the pipe. You see cockroaches crawling on the walls of the pipe. You see a rat snake slithering through the pipe.

Rooms.Name: The Southern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large pipe that is covered in slime and moss. There is a foul smell coming from the pipe. You see rats running around the pipe. You see a dead fish in the pipe. You see a bat flying in the pipe.

Rooms.Name: A Narrow Passage North
Rooms.Description: You see a passage that is too narrow for horses, but just right for pedestrians. The passage is bordered on each side by brick walls, and there is a metal gate at the entrance. Inside, the passage is illuminated by torches, and you can see that it is clean and well-maintained.

Rooms.Name: A Rotting Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a dark, dank, and smelly sewer pipe that is clearly in need of repair or replacement. There is trash and debris strewn about, and the pipe itself is cracked and broken in places. The smell is overwhelming, and you can hear the sound of rats scurrying around. This is not a pleasant place to be, and you would not recommend spending any time here unless absolutely necessary.

Rooms.Name: A Rotting Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large, metal pipe that is filled with sewage and water. The pipe is old and rusty, and there is trash and debris floating in the water. The smell is overpowering, and you can hear the sound of rats scurrying around.

Rooms.Name: A Murky Pool
Rooms.Description: The water is murky and there is debris floating in it. The bottom of the pool is not visible. There are stairs leading into the water.

Rooms.Name: A Drainage Gate
Rooms.Description: You see a large, metal gate that is meant to block water from flowing through. There is a small gap at the bottom of the gate where water can seep through. The gate is rusted and has been worn down over time.

Rooms.Name: A Drainage Gate
Rooms.Description: You see a large, metal gate that is slightly ajar. Beyond the gate, You see a concrete drainage ditch that is filled with water. The ditch is flanked by a rocky embankment. There is a metal grate in the center of the gate.

Rooms.Name: Within a Grand Cave
Rooms.Description: You see a large cave with a high ceiling. The cave is lit up with bright lights, and you can see various rock formations and stalactites and stalagmites. There is a path through the cave that you can follow. You also see some bats hanging from the ceiling.

Rooms.Name: The Southern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: The southern sewer pipe is a large pipe that runs through the city of Griffonshire. It is made of concrete and is several feet in diameter. There is a large opening at the top of the pipe that allows water to flow into it. The pipe is filled with water and is used to transport sewage from the city to the ocean.

Rooms.Name: A Southeasterly Sewer Drain
Rooms.Description: You see a sewer drain that is full of trash and debris. The water is murky and there is a strong smell of sewage. There are rats scurrying around, and the overall atmosphere is dirty and unpleasant.

Rooms.Name: Within a Grand Cave
Rooms.Description: You see a large cave with a deep pool of water inside. There are several large rocks and a few small trees inside the cave. The water is clear and there are fish swimming in it. The cave is cool and dark, and there is a musty smell.

Rooms.Name: The Southern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: The southern sewer pipe in the City of Griffonshire is a large pipe that runs underground. It is made of concrete and is very dirty. There is a strong smell of sewage coming from it.

Rooms.Name: A Southeasterly Sewer Drain
Rooms.Description: You see a dark, dank sewer drain that smells of sewage and rotting garbage. There is a small trickle of water flowing through it, and rats scurry around in the shadows. The walls are slimy and covered in mold, and the air is thick and stagnant.

Rooms.Name: A Narrow Cave Passage
Rooms.Description: You see a narrow cave passage that is dark and damp. The walls are covered in moss and there is a small stream of water running through the middle of the passage. You can hear the sound of dripping water and the sound of bats somewhere in the distance.

Rooms.Name: The Southern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a large pipe that is spewing out sewage. The pipe is surrounded by a fence, and there is a sign that says "Danger: Do not enter." There is a strong smell of sewage, and the ground is covered in a slimy substance.

Rooms.Name: A Shimmering Quartz Cavern
Rooms.Description: You see a large cavern made of shimmering quartz. The quartz reflects the light in the cavern, making it appear to shimmer. The cavern is also filled with rocks of all sizes.

Rooms.Name: The Dragon's Hoard
Rooms.Description: You stand amid a massive hoard that is occupied by a very irritated looking dragon. The hoard glimmers and shines with riches under your torchlight.

Rooms.Name: A Waste Pit
Rooms.Description: You see a dark and dreary pit that is full of trash and debris. The stench is unbearable and the sight is repulsive. There is no life to be found here, only filth and grime. This is a place that has been forgotten by society, a place where people come to dump their unwanted junk.

Rooms.Name: A Fork in the Caves
Rooms.Description: You see a long, dark cave with a small stream running through it. There are stalactites and stalagmites throughout the cave, and the air is cool and damp. You hear the sound of running water and the occasional drip of water from the ceiling.

Rooms.Name: The Southern Sewer Pipe
Rooms.Description: You see a dark, dank sewer pipe that is obviously well used. There is trash and debris strewn about, and the smell is incredibly foul. You can hear the sound of rats scurrying around, and the occasional drip of water. The pipe is large enough for a person to walk through, but you would not recommend it.

Rooms.Name: Among Stalactites
Rooms.Description: You see HUGE stalactites! And they are so close together that you can barely walk through them. The ground is uneven and there are lots of slippery rocks, so you have to be careful not to fall. The air is damp and musty, and the light is dim. But it's really cool to be in this place.

Rooms.Name: The Mouth of a Cavern
Rooms.Description: You see a dark, damp cave with a small stream of water running through it. The cave is illuminated by a few small lights, and you can see stalactites and stalagmites throughout the cave. There is a metal grate covering the entrance to the cave, and a sign that says "DO NOT ENTER."

Rooms.Name: A Tunnel Full of Trash
Rooms.Description: A garbage chute in the sewer is a long, dark, and smelly place. There is trash and garbage everywhere, and it is difficult to walk without stepping on something. The air is thick with the smell of garbage, and it is difficult to breathe. The walls are covered in graffiti, and there is trash and garbage piled up to the ceiling. It is a dirty, dangerous, and unpleasant place to be.

Rooms.Name: A Narrow Cave Passageway
Rooms.Description: You see a narrow cave passageway that is dark and damp. The walls are slimy and there are bats flying around. You can hear the sound of dripping water and You can see a small stream of water running through the passage.

Rooms.Name: Walking Along A Wide Drainage
Rooms.Description: You see a wide drainage ditch that is full of water. The water is flowing slowly and there is some debris in the water. There is slim, mold, and dark green moss growing along the edges.

Rooms.Name: Walking Along A Wide Drainage
Rooms.Description: You see a large drainage pipe with a concrete walkway next to it. The walkway is wide enough for two people to walk side by side. There is a brick wall on one side of the walkway, and on the other side is laid stone masonry. The drainage pipe is about four feet in diameter and is made of concrete. There is a small stream of water flowing through the pipe.

Rooms.Name: Walking Along A Wide Drainage
Rooms.Description: You see a wide drainage ditch with concrete walls. The ditch is full of water and there is a strong smell of sewage. There are rats swimming in the water and there is trash floating on the surface.

Rooms.Name: Walking Along A Wide Drainage
Rooms.Description: You see a wide drainage ditch with concrete walls. The ditch is filled with water and there is a pipe running along the bottom of it. There is a sidewalk along the side of the ditch. There is dark moss and mold.

Rooms.Name: Within a Cavern
Rooms.Description: You see darkness and shadows while walking in or within a cavern in the in the sewers. You may see some light shining in from above, but it is usually dim. You feel a sense of foreboding while walking in this place.

Rooms.Name: A Natural Cavern
Rooms.Description: You see a large, dark cavern with a few small openings at the top that allow light to enter. There are several stalactites and stalagmites throughout the cavern, and a small stream of water flows through the center. The air is cool and damp, and the cavern is very quiet.

Rooms.Name: A Trash Heap
Rooms.Description: You see a trash heap that is full of garbage. There is a strong smell of garbage and it is difficult to breathe. The trash heap is full of flies and maggots. There are rats running around and the ground is covered in garbage.

Rooms.Name: A Natural Cavern
Rooms.Description: You see a large, dark cavern with stalactites and stalagmites. There is a small river running through the cavern, and the air is cool and damp. You see bats and spiders hanging from the ceiling, and small creatures scurrying along the ground. The cavern is lit by a few small lights, and you can hear the drip of water echoing in the space.

Rooms.Name: A Natural Cavern
Rooms.Description: You see a large, dark cavern. There are stalactites and stalagmites throughout the space. You hear the drip of water and the sound of bats. You see a small pool of water in the center of the space. There is a small opening at the top of the cavern that lets in a shaft of light.

Rooms.Name: A Gated Sewer Exit
Rooms.Description: You see a gated sewer exit. The gate is made of metal and is rusty. There is a hole in the gate that is big enough for a person to fit through. The hole is surrounded by sharp metal. There is a sign on the gate that says "Danger, do not enter".
